# Job Agent

An automated AI-powered job search agent that scrapes multiple job boards daily, filters listings against your requirements using **Gemini 2.5 Flash via Vertex AI**, finds key contacts at target companies, saves results to Firebase Firestore, and delivers a rich digest to Slack.

Runs on a **near-zero budget** using GitHub Actions, Vertex AI, and Firebase.

---

## How It Works

```
GitHub Actions (cron: weekdays)
        │
        ▼
Scrape 5 Job Boards in Parallel
(Greenhouse, Lever, Ashby, RemoteOK, WeWorkRemotely — no login needed)
        │
        ▼
Deduplicate Against Firestore
(skips jobs already seen or previously rejected)
        │
        ▼
Gemini 2.5 Flash via Vertex AI — Filter & Score
(matches against your stack, seniority, location, visa requirements)
        │
        ▼
Hunter.io — Find Key Contacts (optional)
(engineering managers, recruiters at target companies)
        │
        ▼
Firebase Firestore — Save Matches + Rejections
        │
        ▼
GitHub Actions (cron: midday weekdays)
Slack Digest — Rich Block Kit message with scores, reasoning, apply buttons
        │
        ▼
Firebase Cloud Function
Slack /jobs slash command — query your leads on demand
```

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Tool | Cost |
|---|---|---|
| Scheduler | GitHub Actions | Free |
| Scraping | Greenhouse, Lever, Ashby, RemoteOK, WWR public APIs | Free |
| AI Filtering | Gemini 2.5 Flash via Vertex AI | ~$0.01–0.05/day |
| Database | Firebase Firestore | Free (50k reads / 20k writes/day) |
| Contact Lookup | Hunter.io | Free (25 searches/month) |
| Notifications | Slack Incoming Webhooks | Free |
| Slash Command | Firebase Cloud Functions | Free (2M invocations/month) |

---

## Project Structure

```
job-agent/
├── .github/
│   └── workflows/
│       ├── scrape.yml          # Scrapes + saves — runs weekday mornings with manual trigger
│       └── notify.yml          # Sends Slack digest — runs weekday midday with manual trigger
├── src/
│   ├── scrapers/
│   │   ├── greenhouse.ts       # Greenhouse ATS public API
│   │   ├── lever.ts            # Lever ATS public API
│   │   ├── ashby.ts            # Ashby ATS public API
│   │   ├── remoteok.ts         # RemoteOK public API
│   │   ├── weworkremotely.ts   # WeWorkRemotely RSS feed
│   │   └── index.ts            # Aggregates all scrapers
│   ├── agent.ts                # Main entry — scrape → deduplicate → filter → save
│   ├── config.ts               # All configuration lives here
│   ├── contacts.ts             # Hunter.io contact lookup
│   ├── db.ts                   # Firestore read/write helpers
│   ├── notify.ts               # Slack digest sender
│   └── types.ts                # Shared TypeScript interfaces
├── functions/
│   └── src/
│       └── index.ts            # Firebase Cloud Function — Slack /jobs command
├── .env                        # Local only — never commit this
├── .env.example                # Template — commit this
├── .gitignore
├── tsconfig.json
└── package.json
```

---

## Prerequisites

- Node.js 22+
- npm
- Firebase CLI (`npm install -g firebase-tools`)
- A [Firebase project](https://console.firebase.google.com) with Firestore enabled
- A Google Cloud project with [Vertex AI API](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/aiplatform.googleapis.com) enabled
- A Slack workspace where you can create apps
- A [Hunter.io](https://hunter.io) account (optional)

---

## Setup

### 1. Clone & Install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/job-agent.git
cd job-agent
npm install
```

### 2. Firebase Setup

```bash
firebase login
firebase init firestore   # Select your existing project
firebase init functions   # Choose TypeScript, say Yes to install deps
```

### 3. Enable Vertex AI

Go to [console.cloud.google.com](https://console.cloud.google.com) → your project → **APIs & Services** → search for **Vertex AI API** → **Enable**.

Your Firebase service account is used to authenticate with Vertex AI automatically — no separate API key needed.

### 4. Environment Variables

Copy the example file:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Then fill in your `.env`:

```bash
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT=   # Minified JSON — see below
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=          # Incoming webhook URL
SLACK_VERIFICATION_TOKEN=   # For the /jobs slash command
HUNTER_API_KEY=             # Optional
```

#### Where to get each value

| Variable | Where |
|---|---|
| `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT` | Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service Accounts → Generate new private key → minify to one line: `cat key.json \| tr -d '\n'` |
| `SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL` | [api.slack.com/apps](https://api.slack.com/apps) → Your App → Incoming Webhooks → Add New Webhook |
| `SLACK_VERIFICATION_TOKEN` | Same Slack app → Basic Information → App Credentials → Verification Token |
| `HUNTER_API_KEY` | [hunter.io](https://hunter.io) → Dashboard → API (optional — agent works without it) |


### 5. GitHub Actions Secrets

Go to your repo → **Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions** and add the same variables as repository secrets.

### 6. Deploy the Slack Slash Command

```bash
cd functions
npm install
cd ..
firebase deploy --only functions
```

Copy the printed function URL. Then in your Slack app:
- **Slash Commands** → **Create New Command**
- Command: `/jobs`
- Request URL: your Firebase Function URL
- Save

---

## Configuration

**Everything is configured from a single file: `src/config.ts`**

This is the only file you need to edit to personalise the agent for your own job search.

```ts
export const config = {
  model: 'gemini-2.5-flash',
  matchScoreThreshold: 7,       // minimum match score out of 10

  requirements: {
    roles: ['Frontend Developer', 'Full-stack Developer', 'Web Team Lead'],
    stack: ['Vue.js', 'Nuxt.js', 'TypeScript', 'React', 'Next.js', 'Firebase'],
    seniority: 'Mid to Senior',
    location: 'Your City, Country (Timezone: GMT+X)',
    remotePreference: [
      'HIGH PRIORITY: Fully Remote (Worldwide or EMEA-based)',
    ],
    relocationPolicy: [
      'Only consider non-remote roles IF they explicitly offer visa sponsorship.',
    ],
    exclude: ['Project Manager', 'Product Manager'],
  },

  keywords: ['frontend', 'vue', 'react', 'nuxt', 'full stack', 'typescript'],

  // Companies to scrape per ATS — find more at boards.greenhouse.io/<slug>
  greenhouse: ['airbnb', 'stripe', 'notion', 'figma', 'linear', 'vercel'],
  lever: ['netflix', 'shopify', 'atlassian', 'discord', 'canva'],
  ashby: ['ramp', 'mercury', 'retool', 'brex', 'loom'],

  maxJobsPerDigest: 20,
};
```

---

## Running Locally

```bash
# Scrape jobs and save matches to Firestore
npm run scrape

# Send Slack digest of unnotified jobs
npm run notify
```

