| `/jobs today` | Show leads found today |
| `/jobs help` | Show all commands |

---

## Adding More Companies

Find out which ATS a company uses by checking their careers page URL:

| URL pattern | ATS | Config key |
|---|---|---|
| `boards.greenhouse.io/company` | Greenhouse | `config.greenhouse` |
| `jobs.lever.co/company` | Lever | `config.lever` |
| `jobs.ashbyhq.com/company` | Ashby | `config.ashby` |

For RemoteOK and WeWorkRemotely, all jobs are scraped and filtered by keyword — no company list needed.

---

## How Deduplication Works

The agent maintains two Firestore collections:

- `job_leads` — matched jobs (score ≥ threshold)
- `rejected_leads` — jobs scraped but below the match threshold

Before sending any job to Vertex AI, it checks both collections. Jobs already in either collection are skipped — so you never pay to analyse the same listing twice and you never see the same job in your digest twice.

---

## Free Tier Limits

| Service | Limit | Estimated Usage |
|---|---|---|
| GitHub Actions | 2,000 min/month | ~80 min/month |
| Vertex AI | Pay per token | ~$0.01–0.05/day |
| Firestore | 50k reads / 20k writes/day | Well within limits |
| Hunter.io | 25 searches/month | Only runs on matched jobs |
| Slack Webhooks | Unlimited | Free |
| Firebase Functions | 2M invocations/month | Slash command only |

